                <h1>Who Opposed George W. Bush in 2000: A Look at Al Gore</h1>
                <p>In the 2000 presidential election, George W. Bush ran against Democratic candidate Al Gore. The race was one of the closest in U.S. history, ultimately hinging on the results in Florida, where a contentious recount led to a Supreme Court decision. The election raised questions about voting systems and election integrity.</p>
